title: For Sale:  Hammerli 208 S (S model, not 208 International)
location: Far NE IL, or NH, New Hampshire, United States
postcontent:
Hammerli 208 S, the end version of the legendary 20 /International, offers a 2 stage trigger with adjustable trigger position.
The basic sight system, and interchangeable barrel weights with rail that can accept an optical sight mount were retained.
Important note: some have said the Armslist email system is NOT forwarding inquiries. If you receive no response within a day, please email directly at REDACTED, or start by emailing directly.
The model offered is a commemorative version. Same as the other S models, but with a better finish, and gold lettering. The Morini grip is original to the gun, and has been modified slightly to correct the problems with the stock Morini grip shelf. The S model uses a modified trigger system from the older 208, but basically a similar trigger to the 215 and the later 208 guns. These changes were made to reduce production cost. Trigger quality was not improved, but was not decreased either.
Like the S&W41, the 208 and the S model evolved from the Walther Olympia of the 1930s, which itself was an adaptation of the Reising Target Pistol. After an unsuccessful adaptation by Hammerli following WWII as the Hammerli Walther Olympia, the International saw the gun revised extensive with a far superior result. The 208, and by pass-through of the inheritance, is, in essence, the ultimate S&W41 that Smith and Wesson never made. The barrel is a solid unit with the frame, with superb (close to 0.5 MOA) accuracy resulting.
The trigger is excellent for consistency, and readily adjustable from about 400 gms to about 3000. In addition to having a "fine" adjustment, this gun offers a coarse adjustment system for rapid adjustment from heavy to light pull weights. The S model is slightly less accurate than the older 208 guns, but the difference is very difficult to detect, and many prefer the S due to the adjustable trigger position and 2 stage option. Gun weight can be adjusted by change in barrel weights (0-240 gm available). The original Hammerli grip is one of the best ever offered for a handgun. Additional magazines (OEM Hammerli) available, and optional weights as above. This gun is NOT a SigArms import, and has no safety. Email if other images needed.
Also available are :
Steyr Match pistol .22lr (R or LH grip)
Full nickel factory plated Walther GSP in .22lr/32,
Hammerli Sig P240 in all 3 calibers (.38, .32, .22lr)
Hammerli SIG P240 in .32 SWLWC Hammerli 208 international (2 slightly different guns)
Hammerli 150 (L or RH grip) Walther GSP, Walther OSP (all versions, 10" barrel)
Hi Standard Victors (Hamden, Hartford, 5.5" barrels only)
Whitney marked WOLVERINE, & one typical, not wolverine-marked
M96 Swedish Mauser in 6.5x55 with Elit diopter sights, target trigger, and pistol grip (yes, those did exist for this rifle), with Norma sniper/match ammo
 
Many of the other guns are under Listings by this User which also is
http://www.armslist.com/classifieds/search?relatedto=4574568
 
Transfer can be on an IL FOID card after state police approval, or to NH residents with any of the several forms of ID acceptable there. Shipping to FFL holder for transfer also is available. Shipping is free on this gun. Additional guns can be combined, on some of them with a 10% discount when combined in the same shipment.
I am not a gun dealer, do not accept credit cards or general requests/special orders for guns, do not purchase or acquire guns primarily or specifically to resell them, do not have regular store hours, and do not accept trades except for guns that I would acquire otherwise for personal use. All guns have been my property for time periods ranging from many decades to at least several years, and all have been used by me in various activities. The guns offered are those that now are "surplus" from my collection or "pattern library" and no longer are needed for personal use or as reference standards. Requests are accepted for guns not listed just in case the request matches another gun that is in my holdings and is scheduled for future listing, but has not been listed yet. No other types of requests are accepted. All guns sold by me are re-tested for function and accuracy before sale to others.  In addition to being surplus sales from personal collection or holdings, the main thing being sold is not the gun itself, but information regarding what gun might be optimal for your needs.
The guns, and I, vary in location between far NE IL, and SE NH.
